<h1><a href="/2013/09/25/A-Windy-City-Status-Update/">A Windy City Status Update</a></h1>
<p>Posted at 25 Sep 2013 by staff</p>
</div>
<div class="share-btns">
<div>
<a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-via="devbootcamp">Tweet</a>
</div>
<div>
<div id="fb-root"></div>
<div class="fb-like" data-send="false" data-layout="button_count" data-width="1" data-show-faces="false" data-action="like"></div>
</div>
<div>
<script class="linkedin-share" type="IN/Share" data-counter="right" data-showzero="true"></script>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="article-post">
<p><img src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-dVHy1rX9ybo/Tqn_rNYcAqI/AAAAAAAAFP4/7saDMCHTXU8/s1600/chicago.jpg" alt="code" height="470" width="700"></p>
<p>For the last 5 months, Dev Bootcamp Chicago has been launching newly minted junior developers into the midwestern software ecosystem and beyond. The program is structured the same as San Francisco, with new cohorts of students graduating every 3 weeks.</p>
<p>Earlier this week, DBC co-founder and Chicago head Dave Hoover shared a bit of what's happened in that time over on <a href="http://www.builtinchicago.org/blog/dev-bootcamp-grads-hit-job-market">Built In Chicago</a>.</p>
<h2>By the numbers</h2>
<p>Like in our San Francisco program, we're seeing great results on the hiring front:<br></p>
<p>5 graduated cohorts<br>
70 students<br>
90% of the first cohort employed<br>
$70ks average salary of graduates<br></p>
<h2>Beyond the numbers</h2>
<p>Groupon, Eight Bit, BrightTag, Sprout Social, NCSA, Instructure, Braintree, Mondo Robot, Clinkle - <em>some of the companies where our students have landed</em><br>
Chicago, Austin, San Francisco, Boulder, Minneapolis, New York City - <em>a few of the cities where graduates have relocated - although many are choosing to stay in Chicago</em><br>
<a href="http://heygirl.io">HeyGirl.io</a> - a student project from <a href="http://twitter.com/keccers">Katherine Champagne</a> that went viral while she was in cohort<br>
<a href="https://github.com/rwarbelow/the_swot_bot/tree/master">The SWOTBOT</a> - standing for "Scholars Working OverTime," a fully functional classroom management system build as a final project and now used every day in the classroom of alumni <a href="Rachel%20Warbelow">Rachel Warbelow</a></p>
<p>We love seeing how the Chicago community is thriving in similar ways to our San Francisco graduates, all while developing its own unique and inspiring culture, and can't wait to see what comes of future cohorts.</p>
<p>To read more, check out <a href="http://www.builtinchicago.org/blog/dev-bootcamp-grads-hit-job-market">"Dev Bootcamp Grads Hit The Job Market"</a></p>
</div>
</div>
